name: Matt Croydon
tweet: @mjwhansen You could probably put one with a flat bottom on the desk but need to be careful about reflections up. I’ve seen some where the shield mounts on the boom and the mic inside. There’s also the classic NPR pillow fort:  https://t.co/Fry4S0stTz

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: @mjwhansen It’s dynamic and if it’s on a boom you’re already doing a great job. Blankets and softness are probably your next steps. Those mini isolation booths can do the same thing with more convenience.

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: @mjwhansen Some great replies here. Getting the mic up off the desk and near your mouth helps a ton. If you have a condenser mic like a blue yeti you might try borrowing a dynamic mic to see if that helps. Condensers are great but pick up everything.

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: So. If this is how they approach selling physical stuff on the internet, which is pretty far away from what they do for a living, how do you think they approach their core business?

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: A24 makes movies. Netflix distributes content (and makes movies).

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: Burying the lede a bit here: what strikes me most about both of these experiences is *how far outside* their core competencies online shopping is.

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: The A24 tray, made by @Cambro1, came in a super detailed and retro-looking box. Even nicer than the box it was packed inside. The receipt lay inside an A24 folio similar to one you might receive your invoice in at a nice hotel.

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: There were definitely some common traits. The boxes were thick. High quality. Not the cheap stuff. The Netflix shirt came folded and wrapped in tissue paper. Netflix tissue paper.

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: Fast forward a few days. Stuff starts showing up on my doorstep and in my mailbox. I ended up unboxing these two items back to back.

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: I used Apple Pay here. I love Apple Pay. I could have used Shop Pay too, or entered my information manually like a madman.

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: The site is gorgeous to look at on desktop or mobile. It does a great job of providing context about the content, the product, and the creators.

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: I was here for this BEAMS x EDEN shirt that I couldn’t let go of.  https://t.co/OPMKq9xSdK

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: Let’s not forget  https://t.co/JLtteyfK7p. It’s a recent popup featuring collabs between Netflix and artists/brands with collections inspired by recent anime hits Eden and Yasuke.

name: Matt Croydon
tweet: The checkout process was a breeze on my phone, of course. I used Shop Pay. I love Shop Pay.
